  <original-body>I am running Rails 2.3.3 with Ruby 1.8.6p383 and have discovered when I am using:

&lt;code&gt;
form_for [@user, @article] do |f|
&lt;/code&gt;
with the following routing:
&lt;code&gt;
map.resources :users do |user|
    user.resources :articles
end
map.resources :articles
&lt;/code&gt;

I am getting the generated &lt;form&gt;-urls for the action: 
- new  action=&quot;/users/1/articles&quot; ...
- edit action=&quot;articles/100&quot; ...

Why cant I get also for the action???
- edit action=&quot;/users/1/articles/100&quot; ...

Then I - could - say in my routing:
&lt;code&gt;
map.resources :users do |user|
    user.resources :articles
end
map.resources :articles, :only =&gt; [:index, :show]
&lt;/code&gt;

Unfortuantely, I still have to write the unclear und unclean way:

&lt;code&gt;
map.resources :articles, :only =&gt; [:index, :show, :update]
&lt;/code&gt;</original-body>
